<br>
It's main flaw, to me, seems that there aren't really many (or any) truly random encounters.  <br>
<br>
If I know where the graveyard is, I can just waltz a sun cleric down in there and just pick my nose while undead explode.<br>
<br>
What's that you say?  A spider cavern is out in the woods?  Okay, I'll park my plant cleric there and do the same thing.<br>
<br>
There's never bandits in the graveyard, or wizards in the spider cavern, or any of the stuff you would need to &quot;mix it up&quot; enough that you can't tailor a character for a certain area and then level insanely fast.<br>
<br>
I do frequently see servers that &quot;solve&quot; this problem by turning down advancement (so that a skeleton only gives you 3 XP or whatever)... but this does not seem like a solution.  The game hasn't become more challenging, it's just become more boring.<br>
<br>
